course_title: Women's Health Nurse Practitioner II: Advanced Care of Women
course_description: Students will gain the knowledge/skills to recognize health deviations in obstetrical care that impact the care, families, and lives of women in a variety of settings. Within these settings, the student will learn to perform comprehensive, advanced health assessments of childbearing women.
prerequisites: NRSG 600 or equivalent transfer credit as prerequisite.
